column2: i began to have cyber relations with a 25 year old man. he told me that i was his soulmate and he wanted to urinate on me to profess his love. i ended things because i knew something about it was wrong & he then threatened to kill himself. sergio p.
i had a flashback of an older cousin forcing me to perform oral sex at a very early age. i waited 9 years before asking my mom about it.
my first time performing oral sex was through force and intimidation by a college sophomore. javonte m.
i was cornered by 3 other students. they kept laughing about how far aj's fingers would go up my vagina. it was just us. that was one of the scariest moments of my life. luckily the bell rang. ...
a coach at my high school gave me a $100 with a note saying it was going to be our year. he invited me to the movies. jamele h.

my first vaginal sex experience was forced by a childhood friend a year older than me. he raped me. afterwards he said ""i couldn't let them *** at famu get to you first.... how does it feel to be a woman?"" later on i confronted him and he told me i was a liar and that i wanted it. at a much earlier point
column3: he told me that he lost his virginity to a woman at least in her 30's. michael n.

column2: i went to a classmates house to tutor him in physics. i got very drunk. he raped me. later on he acknowledged and apologized for his actions. very very healing & therapeutic. as.

column1: from age 18-20 i was involved in an emotionally abusive situation. he asked me how could i be so dumb to get raped twice. sam h.
for the last few years i've had recurring dreams of confronting mike
column2: because his betrayal hurt me the most. i included my experiences with older men because of recent convos on r kelly. these situations are happening everyday and they are real & serious. believe us! -crystal lipscomb parker""

column1: emma charlotte duerre watson (born 15 april 1990) is an english actress
column3: and activist. born in paris and brought up in oxfordshire
column4: watson attended the dragon school and trained as an actress at the oxford branch of stagecoach theatre arts. as a child artist
column5: she rose to prominence after landing her first professional acting role as hermione granger in the harry potter film series
column6: having acted only in school plays previously. watson appeared in all eight harry potter films from 2001 to 2011

column2: the actress captured everyone's attention with her moving speech in front of the united nations that launched a new initiative for gender equality. watson's work for the un reminded us all that feminism isn't just a fight for womenâ€”it's for men to join in as well. since
column4: her own feminist book club and plenty of conversation about what it means to be a feminist today. @emmawatson .

column1: 59393;instagram;2019-01-26 22:23:55;FALSE;"i've never needed a salt bath more than i had a few nights ago! after a series of challenging interactions with both my son and my partner
column2: and diving deep into my own wounds and triggers felt it was time .. time to release... ***tw: sexual assault *** ... it was the night #metoo went viral and i has invited a lover over for the evening. we had the house to itself and we spent the night painting lightbulb for the house. the sexual encounter began consentually and very quickly shifted into a realm i would not have given my consent if asked.. it was excruciating and i disassociate.. hard.. we went for breakfast the next day and i drove him home.. he blocked me and i hurt physically for a week after
column3: went catatonic for nearly a month with the exception of doing the bare minimum of feeding obie and getting him to daycare... the year that followed has seen me in many healing ceremonies
column7: tipi meetings and more to bring compassion
column8: forgiveness and healing. it's also seen a rise in anxiety
column9: and getting triggered to the point of panic attack and very physiological responses to my trauma. this has effected not only my relationships but my ability to mother in a deeply connective way getting frequently triggered by my own sons affection.... between the loving support i have received from my partner holding me and loving me through my triggers.. and obie telling me how it hurts him when i push him away.. i felt strong enough to finally let it all go. i was finally fortified to face the final ceremony and spent the better part in the day burning the life candle of my abuser.. clearing the multigenational pattern of sexual abuse going back to to the residential schools that we both share lineage to.. deeply forgiving until there was nothing left to forgive.. until his candle went out.. and my year old blood was spilled into the pristine snow to nourish my cherry tree.. and finally.. the salt bath. completion. peace. .... this april i will be co-facilitating a weekend retreat for women. survivors of sexual trauma.. to heal
column11: reclaim and disarmour. if this speaks to you and you want more info please reach out.

column3: please call and leave a message for east middle school this weekend
column4: so the administration returns on monday to a very full inbox. you will get various options for who to be connected to when you call. â€œprincipalâ€ wasnâ€™t an option
column5: so i chose â€œschool psychologist.â€ it rang through and then i was transferred to a general voicemail. ideas on what to say (iâ€™m speaking from my experience as a white person
column6: to be clear): l told them how disappointed and sad i am that they traumatized four students who will be forever impacted by their racism and horrendous judgement
column7: and how their lack of accountability makes it 1000 times worse. i told them that i was hyper and giddy at school with my friends when i was 12
column8: and my white skin means not only did i not get in trouble

column2: so when i say i didn't have much freedom because i'm a girl
column4: so i don't need to go into detail. the first time i sneaked out was when i was 16. it was with a friend. we were going on a bike. and even though she was the one riding
column5: i felt like i was in charge. in charge of which road to take. incharge of myself. i mean i could go anywhere right now if i want to. that littlest act of courage and dareness made me realize the goodness i'd been missing. i didn't go out to do anything wrong. just to a decent restaurant and shopping. i felt free. really free. i don't know how to express it. it made my heart swell to tears back then. she was used to going out and i was happy that she was not one of us girls
column6: but she didn't realize how much it meant to me. nor did i tell her. i remember the date very clearly. and that brought the biggest change in my life ever. its been years since then
column7: i know how to get my way now. a taste of freedom is all it took to learn how to fight for myself.

column1: 59754;instagram;2019-01-26 15:13:18;FALSE;"i'm posting this for a few reasons
column2: now allow me to explain. i am chubby. i have a very hard time losing weight no matter what i do. i'll change how i eat
column3: i work out. nothing helps and i just struggle. i do what i can to feel good in my skin but it is hard. i'll look in the mirror wanting to vomit
column4: and then in another i'll feel amazing. that is thanks to my borderline. people feel the need to tell girls they are sluts if they feel comfortable in their own skin
column5: especially when posting photos like this. we are not sluts. if i post something like this i am not asking for attention. it means i actually felt good about how i looked. that my chub was cute. that i didnt hate myself. another thing is i do not owe anyone anything. if i say you need to stop blowing up my phone
column6: dont come back saying you would have a field day making me feel bad for it. if i say no to kissing or sex. that means no. do not guilt trip me into doing it. do not continue to try and just fucking respect me not wanting it. i have a lot of mental illnesses and they kill me. every day they bring me down but i try hard not allowing that to happen. it's as simple as me wanting to post more on here
column7: but fearing everyone hates me and my content is shit. like this. will people just comment saying i am gross? will this be something no one even reads? who cares? to me this is important. i am more than my chub or what is between my legs. i am a human. and i deserve to be respected. .

column1: 59911;instagram;2019-01-26 13:31:04;FALSE;"july 2014 my ex-husband brought to life my worst fear. raping me. i painted a lighthouse not realize i was searching for light in a dark place.

column2: i was asked to paint my happy place. i painted a sunset with the sun being a clock and pictures of my boys in the center. i didnâ€™t even realize what it meant until some brought it to my attention. the clock sun shows it takes time to heal.

column1: in 2016 i made the painting with the fairy being set free from a cage. this was the year my ex-husband went to the brig.

i did the hardest thing any victim could. i got up in the court marshal hearing and testified of all the things that were kept behind doors for to long. for the first time i was able to speak and he couldnâ€™t keep me silent.
he was found guilty 6 out of 8 charges. most were against me.
the fairy represents me being set free from his grasp to start my journey of healing.
i still struggle with ptsd from all the abuse but i am getting better. it takes a lot of courage for a victim to speak out
column2: to move from being a victim to a survivor. if you are in a domestic violence relationship or know someone who is remember you can get out and you can be the light to help that person get out.
